POP3 client that allows unsecured connection or secured connection via TLS or SSL.
USAGE: popcl <server> [-p <port>] [-T|-S [-c <certfile>] [-C <certaddr>]] [-d] [-n] -a <auth_file> -o <out_dir>
	where: 	<server> - address of server
		[-p <port>] - optional argument, server port
		[-T|-S] - optional argument, -T = SSL, -S = TLS
		[-c <certfile>] - optional argument, file with certificate
		[-C <certaddr>] - optional argument, certificate store
		[-d] - optional argument, delete messages after read
		[-n] - optional argument, download only locally unread messages
		-a <auth_file> - mandatory argument, authentification file in format of "username = <>\npassword = <>"
		-o <out_dir> - mandatory argument, existing directory to deposit email files

	
